Adds the server-side entity a chat has never had (chats table) plus a
1:1 goals table so a chat can carry a named goal the way a Claude
Project carries custom instructions:

- goals.title / successMetric / valueInr / deadline are all required
  before a goal is considered set — these are the only inputs that let
  Venus reason about urgency, expected value, or trade-offs at all.
- venus_decisions gains a nullable chatId so decision/roadmap cards
  generated in a goal-bearing chat are attributable to that goal —
  this is what makes a roadmap item a 'sub-task' of the goal, with no
  separate linking table.
- goals.evidenceScore is a raw, unbounded running score, NOT a
  checked-off task count. Resolving a decision with a positive outcome
  moves it significantly; negative barely moves it (or pulls it
  backward); mixed moves it a little (see goalEvidence.ts). Position on
  the Origin-Target line and at_risk/on_track/off_track are computed
  read-time from this score, never stored as their own state.
- /ai/analyze accepts an optional chatId; when the chat has an active
  goal, its title/metric/value/deadline are injected into the system
  prompt so every answer in that chat is reasoned against it.
- /ai/decisions/:id/outcome now updates the goal's evidenceScore when
  the resolved decision belongs to a goal-bearing chat.
- New /chats, /chats/:id, /chats/:id/goal, /chats/:id/goal/status
  routes (OpenAPI-first: openapi.yaml -> orval codegen for both the
  zod validators and the react-query client).
- Frontend: ChatSession gains an optional serverChatId, created lazily
  on first message (or first goal set) rather than per session, so an
  abandoned chat never leaves an orphan server row. New GoalPanel
  component renders the goal form and the Origin --- Target evidence
  line (soft-compressed past both ends, not clamped, so overshoot and
  setback both stay visible) plus the sub-task list with per-item
  resolved/outcome status instead of a uniform progress bar.

All new/changed packages (lib/db, lib/api-zod, lib/api-client-react,
api-server, vera-nexus) typecheck clean. No DATABASE_URL available in
this environment — schema needs 'drizzle-kit push' against the real
Postgres instance before deploying.
